cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.CV 

The paper discusses stochastic gradient descent (SGD) algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for runtime performance, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The martingale-based analysis used in the paper could be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Asynchronous SGD algorithms are also discussed, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions matrix completion, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
